      "writtenOn": "2021-04-29T13:55:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "One useful feature in Skia is named factories for common operations.  That, in combination with C++ operator overloading yields nice \u0026 fluent code - e.g.\n\n  const auto m \u003d SkMatrix::Translate(10, 10) *\n                 SkMatrix::Scale(2.5, 2.5) *\n                 SkMatrix::RotateDeg(45);\n\nAlas, we don\u0027t get to overload operators here, but named factories would be nice to have still (not necessarily in this CL).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 13,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 13,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "b4eef5cff0fd32e2174f02232e6c23fbbb12e101",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
