        "id": 11964
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-28T19:06:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For operator methods, do we want to have them be non-static like this and modify Matrix A? Or would we prefer static methods that take in 2 matrices and return a new Matrix C?",
      "revId": "b4eef5cff0fd32e2174f02232e6c23fbbb12e101",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1d020fd2_51473382",
        "filename": "platform_tools/android/apps/AndroidKit/src/main/java/org/skia/androidkit/Matrix.java",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 42,
      "author": {
        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-29T13:55:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There might be a place for both.\n\nFor non-static, Skia makes the order super clear with \"pre\"/\"post\" prefixes - e.g. preConcat/postConcat.  So does the current android.graphics.Matrix, so it\u0027s probably a good idea to keep the familiar pattern.\n\nE.g.\n  Matrix a, b;\n  Matrix c \u003d a.preConcat(b);\n  Matrix d \u003d Matrix.Concat(a, b);",
      "parentUuid": "171838e0_1ec4fc04",
      "revId": "b4eef5cff0fd32e2174f02232e6c23fbbb12e101",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e68dcd6a_7ae9f374",
        "filename": "platform_tools/android/apps/AndroidKit/src/main/java/org/skia/androidkit/Matrix.java",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 42,
      "author": {
        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-29T13:55:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"add\" in particular is not very useful in practice.  I suggest we leave it out for now.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 42,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 42,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "b4eef5cff0fd32e2174f02232e6c23fbbb12e101",
